Hi Juri,



the height behavior of CSS is a common pitfall. 100% height only works when
ALL parents are set to a certain height (at least up to a parent with fixed
height set).

And by "all" I really mean including the &lt;html&gt; and the &lt;body&gt;
tag. And including the View which is between the "content" div and the Table.



So actually I'd say you do not need to add a Panel around your TreeTable, just
try

 view.setHeight("100%");

 view.displayBlock(true); // might not yet be available in your version

and add the following style:

html, body {

 margin: 0;

 height: 100%;

}



If it does not work, check all the elements leading down to your Table in the
browser's developer tools.



Regards

Andreas

Hi Sanjiv,



To fire a back-end search Event, you can use an XML HTTP Request from a model
instance.



e.g.



    var myModel = new sap.ui.model.json.JSONModel();
    // attach a Function to catch the asynchronous response
    myModel.attachRequestCompleted( handleSuccess );
    // Fire an XHR to the Service at your Back-end
    // Parameters would be your search query in this case,
    // which you would have to extract at your backend then
    myModel.loadData( ServiceURL, Parameters, true, 'GET' );
    function handleSuccess( oResponse ){
     //handle the response from your Back-end Service e.g.
    myTable.setData( oResponse.data );
    }



Of course the Response of your Service should be in the respective format of
the model you use.



I hope this helps you =) for more details on XHRs you can refer to the
respective Model descriptions here:

 <https://sapui5.netweaver.ondemand.com/sdk/#docs/guide/JSONModel.html>

 <https://sapui5.netweaver.ondemand.com/sdk/#docs/guide/XMLModel.html>

 <https://sapui5.netweaver.ondemand.com/sdk/#docs/guide/ODataModel.html>



Regards,

Jan

