P.S.: The bindRows function expects as a first parameter a string value that
will be used as the binding path. But the "rowContext" is not a string but a
js object. It still contains the path as string in the property "sPath". So if
you want to stick to using the bindRows function, you can try this:



    oTableBPContactNumbers.bindRows(currentRowContext.sPath +"/BusinessPartnerContactNumber");

