Hi Sanket,

if I understood this right, your coding is part of the "view". In that case,
the text property of the label is not "bound" to the model, but contains a
"static" calculated value which will not change if you change your model data.

Therefore I would recommend looking into the data binding with calculated
fields, which can be done with the coding (or check the complete example
above):



    var lblR1Val = new sap.ui.commons.Label({ 
     text : { 
     parts : [ {path : '/TotalPrice', type: new sap.ui.model.type.String()}, 
     {path : '/Currency', type: new sap.ui.model.type.String()}], 
     formatter: function(TotalPrice,Currency){ 
     return TotalPrice+"-"+Currency;
     } 
     } 
    });

More information on this can be found in the developer guide in the chapter
[Calculated Fields for Databinding](https://sapui5.netweaver.ondemand.com/sdk/
#docs/guide/CalcFields.html).

Regards, Frank

