Hi Michael,



Solution is possible, if you retrieve the total no of data rows according to
Model. Please find the below sample source code:



**Step-1:-**



You have to create another model (use same URL which you have used to load
data your table Model) and load data with synchronous way that means "bAsync"
value will be false. You have not mentioned that what type Model you are
using, here I have used XMLModel for example.**  
**



var TableRowCountModel = new sap.ui.model.xml.XMLModel();



// According to API: loadData(sURL, oParameters?, bAsync?, sType?, bCache?,
mHeaders)

TableRowCountModel.loadData("URL", "", false);



**Step-2:-**



Set the new Model into Global level.



sap.ui.getCore().setModel( TableRowCountModel );



**Step-3:-**



Now, use small tricks to get count of proper data node of the model.



var rowCnt = 0;

var kCnt = 1;

for (var i = 0; i &lt; kCnt; i++) {

 try {

 var dimName = TableRowCountModel.getProperty("/Node_Name/" + i
+ "/Sub_Node_Name");

 kCnt++;

 rowCnt++;

 } catch(err) { kCnt = 1; rowCnt = rowCnt - 1; }

}



**"rowCnt" value will give you the result what you are looking for, the count of actual data rows according to Model. See below your modified code:**



for(var k=0;k&lt;**rowCnt**;k++) {

 var thisRow = rows[k];

 ...

 thisRow.getCells()[0].setChecked(false);

}





Hope this will help to fulfill your requirement.







**  
**

Best Regards,

Bibhas Das



