Hi Clark,



Rather than using placeAt directly inside createContent, you should be using
this function simply to return the content of your view, then the view itself
is placed within your page. You could try using the following code in
createContent:





    var oPanel = new sap.ui.commons.Panel({title: new sap.ui.commons.Title({text: "Panel title"})});
    var button = new sap.ui.commons.Button({text:'{/name}'});
    var textField = new sap.ui.commons.TextField("username", { value:'{/name}' });
    oPanel.addContent(button).addContent(textField);
    return oPanel;



Check out [this link
](https://sapui5.netweaver.ondemand.com/sdk/#docs/guide/CreateView.html)for
more information.





Hope this helps.





