Thanks @Frank and @Andreas! Those were really helpful and makes me decide to
investigate further on what's happening inside sap.m.List and the related
components. After digging through the source code, I realized that it is just
spitting &lt;ul&gt; and a bunch of &lt;li&gt; for non-table list which makes
me think that we can just apply css to render it horizontally and apply css
media queries to make it responsive. So my solution is just simply adding
these css:





    .sapMSLI{
     float: left !important;
     display: inline;
     float: left;
     width: 90%;
    }
    @media screen and (min-width: 800px) {
     .sapMSLI{
     width: 40% !important;
     }
     .sapMSLI:nth-child(even){
     float: right;
     margin-left: 2em !important;
     }
    }



Then we can add multiple css media query to support all the devices out there
and our list can automatically change from single column to multiple columns.



