Hi Shen,



Do you mean you want to load the subnodes only after the parent node is
expanded? If so, you could try the [toggleOpenState event ](https://sapui5.net
weaver.ondemand.com/sdk/#docs/api/symbols/sap.ui.commons.TreeNode.html#event:t
oggleOpenState)of the TreeNode. Below is an example (this would obviously
require significant further coding if you want to load your child orgs
recursively for each expanded parent node, but it's just to give you some
idea)...





    oTree.bindAggregation("nodes","/orgList",function(sId,oContext){
     return new sap.ui.commons.TreeNode({ 
     id: oContext.getProperty("orgId"),
     toggleOpenState: function(oEvent) {
     params = oEvent.getParameters();
     if(params.opened==true) { 
     oTreeNode = oEvent.getSource(); 
     customData = oTreeNode.getCustomData();

     var isLoaded = false;
     if(typeof customData[0] != "undefined") {
     isLoaded = customData[0].getValue();
     }

     if(isLoaded==false) { 
     oTreeNode.addNode(new sap.ui.commons.TreeNode({text:"a new subnode"})); 
     oTreeNode.addCustomData(new sap.ui.core.CustomData({key: "loaded", value: true})); 
     }
     } 
     }
     }).bindProperty("text","orgName"); 
    });







the use of CustomData is just to make sure the data is only loaded once









