Ah ok I got you now, I was assuming that each &lt;config&gt; only contained a
single &lt;mode&gt; and &lt;ext&gt;.



If you are sure that the data you want to use will always be in the first
position, you could bind the rows without any filter as follows...





    oTable2.bindRows("/config/0/ext/item");



Alternatively, if you want to actually specify mode=1, one possible technique
you could try (if you haven't already) is filtering and resetting the data
once your model load request is complete...although thinking about it, this
may not necessarily be the best method, especially if you want to use the data
from nodes other than mode=1 as it is resetting your model to contain only the
filtered data..here it is anyway...





    oModel.attachRequestCompleted(function(event) {
     xml = this.getData();
     $(xml).find("config").each(function(){ 
     var mode = this.getElementsByTagName("mode")[0].childNodes[0].nodeValue; 
     if(mode=="1"){ 
     oModel.setXML(new XMLSerializer().serializeToString(this)); 
     return false;
     } 
     });
    })



(you could modify the above to use xpath filtering instead if desired)



...and then of course your binding...





    oTable2.bindRows("/ext/item");
