Hi Ben,



the others already described it correctly: the Button control is not yet added
to the HTML document, so jQuery cannot find it.

Furthermore, UI5 may destroy and re-create the Button HTML when the Button (or
a parent control) is modified and your title attribute would be lost again.



Hence you can use the "onAfterRendering" hook (which is called in both cases):



createContent: function(oController) {

var btnTest = new sap.ui.commons.Button("btnTest", {text : "test"});

return btnTest;

