To expand on my data binding suggestion with an example.



Starting with index.html which creates two views and a model. The model is
attached to the core so it can be used by all the controls.





    <!DOCTYPE HTML>
    <html>
    <head>
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <script src="resources/sap-ui-core.js" id="sap-ui-bootstrap"
     data-sap-ui-libs="sap.ui.commons"
     data-sap-ui-theme="sap_goldreflection">
    </script>
    <script>
     sap.ui.localResources("bindingtest");
     new sap.ui.view({id:"idview11", viewName:"bindingtest.view1", type:sap.ui.core.mvc.ViewType.JS}).placeAt("view1");
     new sap.ui.view({id:"idview21", viewName:"bindingtest.view2", type:sap.ui.core.mvc.ViewType.JS}).placeAt("view2");
     sap.ui.getCore().setModel(new sap.ui.model.json.JSONModel({"setting": "Hello"}));  
    </script>
    </head>
    <body class="sapUiBody" role="application">
     <div id="view1"></div>
     <hr>
     <div id="view2"></div>
    </body>
    </html>



The two views are very similar. View1 renders the model data in a TextField.





     createContent : function(oController) {
     return new sap.ui.commons.layout.HorizontalLayout({
     content : [
      new sap.ui.commons.TextView({ text : "View 1 - " }),
      new sap.ui.commons.TextField({ value : "{/setting}" })
     ]
     });
     }



View2 renders the same model data in a TextView.





     createContent : function(oController) {
     return new sap.ui.commons.layout.HorizontalLayout({
     content : [
      new sap.ui.commons.TextView({ text : "View 2 - " }),
      new sap.ui.commons.TextView({ text : "{/setting}" })
     ]
     });
     }



Now when you change the value in the TextField in view1 it is automatically
updated in the TextView in view2.



