Hi Monica,



It doesn't matter that the link is created dynamically, in your code you just
need to add something like the following:





    function linkPressed(oControlEvent) {
     alert("You clicked on Link " + oControlEvent.getSource().getId());
    };
    //Your code with an extra property added to the link constructor
    for (var i=0; i<aMat.length-1;i++){
    var oLink = new sap.ui.commons.Link({ text: aMat[i].value, press:linkPressed});
    oMatrix.createRow(oLink).
    }



This will register the linkPressed function for each link you create
dynamically, then you can use the getSource method on the oControlEvent to get
the actual link pressed and away you go... you can use any of the methods you
like <http://www.spyvee.com/SAPHTML5_DemoKit/#docs/api/symbols/sap.ui.commons.
Link.html>



